==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Phenicine
<hw>Phen"i*cine</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>foi^nix</grk> purple red: cf. F.
<ets>ph⟦eacute⟧nicine</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd>
<def>A purple powder precipitated when a sulphuric solution of indigo is
diluted with water.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A coloring matter produced
by the action of a mixture of strong nitric and sulphuric acids on
phenylic alcohol.</def> <rj><au>Watts.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Phenicious</ent>⟦br⟧
